Field's Express
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A local train running between Wellington and Palmerston North, leaving Wellington about 6 p.m. Also Field's.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: FIELD, William Hughes MHR Otaki 1900-1911. Born Wanganui 1861, died 1944. Have not yet confirmed Field's Express which has disappeared from the railway literature nor that this is the right Field. Have not yet located an obituary.
