Date:  0/0/1972
Source:  West of the Tararuas
Author:  HOY
Vol / Page:  107
Edition:
Quote:  The former service comprises a Friday night train to Palmerston North, stopping at most stations including those within the suburban area. The latter is a morning and evening return train from Wellington on Sunday. These three trains are all that is left of a twice-daily service which served the district from 1923 to 1958, and which was known as the Field's Express after the Member of Parliament for Otaki (Mr. Field) who campaigned for their introduction.
